# Rules

The most important document you need is [mobile.mdx](../../apps/documentation/src/content/docs/guidelines/mobile.mdx). Always read this file.

## Mobile Development Rules

- Use React Native and Expo for mobile development
- Use React Navigation for navigation (native stack)
- Use NativeWind for styling (Tailwind CSS for React Native)
- Use Zustand for state management
- Use TanStack Query for data fetching
- Use Better Auth for authentication
- Use Lucide React Native for icons only
- Follow the naming conventions in the common guidelines
- Structure features according to the frontend guidelines
- Use react-hook-form with Zod for form validation
- Write unit tests with Jest and React Native Testing Library
- Use EAS for building and deploying

## Environment Variables

- Use `react-native-dotenv` for environment variables
- Prefix public env vars with `EXPO_PUBLIC_`
- Validate env vars with Zod in `config/env.config.ts`

## Navigation

- Use React Navigation native stack
- Define types in `app/navigation/types.ts`
- Use typed navigation hooks from `@react-navigation/native`

## State Management

- Use Zustand for global state
- Structure stores in `store/` directory
- Export store hooks from `store/index.ts`

## Styling

- Use NativeWind for styling
- Follow dark mode best practices with `useTheme` hook
- Use TailwindCSS classes with `className` prop
- Avoid inline styles when possible

## Components

- Create reusable components in `components/` directory
- Feature-specific components go in `features/*/components/`
- Use TypeScript interfaces for props
- Export components from index files
